{"id":484850200,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"1 year, 8 months","timestamp":1619322303,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"92 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/484850200/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"14.5 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        n1 = 0;\n        n2 = 0;\n        cursor = l1;\n        i = 0\n        while cursor != None:\n            n1 += cursor.val * pow(10, i)\n            i += 1\n            cursor = cursor.next;\n        cursor = l2;\n        i = 0\n        while cursor != None:\n            n2 += cursor.val * pow(10, i);\n            i += 1\n            cursor = cursor.next;\n        cursor = ListNode()\n        temp = cursor\n        n1 += n2;\n        while n1 > 0:\n            cursor.val = n1 % 10\n            n1 //= 10\n            if n1 > 0:\n                cursor.next = ListNode()\n                cursor = cursor.next\n        return temp","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"notes":"","topic_tags":[]}
